modules.description: Provides functions to register and load plugins that expose a specific interface, including a string-to-int function. Works with OCaml modules that conform to a predefined plugin signature. Used to dynamically extend application behavior at runtime without recompilation.

Provides functions to load plugins from strings, handle errors through a result type, and inject plugin values into computations. Works with abstract plugin types and error representations. Used to dynamically load and safely execute plugin components while managing failure states.
